---
import FAQCard from "./FAQCard.astro";
---

<section class="flex justify-center bg-black/60 shadow-[inset_0_16px_rgba(0,0,0,0.3)]">
  <div
    class="flex max-w-5xl grow flex-col gap-12 px-4 py-24 text-center text-2xl"
    id="faqsection"
  >
    <h3 class="text-6xl drop-shadow-[0_0_8px_#FF5DA9]">Rundown & FAQ</h3>

    <div class="flex flex-col gap-6">
      <div
        class="space-y-2 overflow-clip bg-dark-bg p-4 text-center text-sm shadow-[6px_6px_rgba(0,0,0,0.3)] motion-safe:transition-transform motion-safe:hover:scale-105 motion-safe:hover:shadow-[8px_8px_rgba(0,0,0,0.3)] lg:space-y-3 lg:p-6"
      >
        <p class="text-2xl leading-6 lg:text-3xl lg:leading-7">
          Date & Time: Starts at 7:00am on November 15 and ends at 7:00pm on November 16.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 md:flex-row">
        <div
          class="flex shadow-[6px_6px_rgba(0,0,0,0.3)] motion-safe:transition-transform motion-safe:hover:scale-105 motion-safe:hover:shadow-[8px_8px_rgba(0,0,0,0.3)] md:w-96 md:flex-col"
        >
          <div
            class="relative w-full space-y-2 overflow-clip bg-dark-bg p-4 text-left text-sm md:w-96 lg:space-y-3 lg:p-6"
          >
            <p class="text-2xl leading-6 lg:text-3xl lg:leading-7">
              Shopify Toronto<br />
               620 King St W<br />
               Toronto, ON M5V 1M6
            </p>

            <svg
              class="absolute right-0 top-0 h-24 w-24 -translate-y-1/3 translate-x-1/3 transform fill-purple-100 opacity-50"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
            >
              <path d="M14 7H10V8H9V12H10V13H14V12H15V8H14V7ZM13 11H11V9H13V11Z"></path>
              <path
                d="M19 4V3H18V2H6V3H5V4H4V15H5V16H6V17H7V18H8V19H9V20H10V21H11V22H13V21H14V20H15V19H16V18H17V17H18V16H19V15H20V4H19ZM18 14H17V15H16V16H15V17H14V18H13V19H11V18H10V17H9V16H8V15H7V14H6V6H7V5H8V4H16V5H17V6H18V14Z"
              ></path>
            </svg>
          </div>

          <img
            class="hidden md:block"
            src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dacrrezls/image/upload/v1711711008/d0458823-92fd-4807-9cb3-83780ae0fd6f_Large_vrcman.jpg"
            alt="People working at tables in a kitchen-style area in an open office."
          />
        </div>

        <div
          class="hidden flex-1 space-y-2 overflow-clip bg-dark-bg text-left text-sm shadow-[6px_6px_rgba(0,0,0,0.3)] md:block lg:space-y-3"
        >
          <iframe
            src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d2887.151920821635!2d-79.40337182375544!3d43.645007471102545!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x882b34de686a1441%3A0x6029a0a7505188d3!2s620%20King%20St%20W%2C%20Toronto%2C%20ON%20M5V%201M6!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sca!4v1711710605246!5m2!1sen!2sca"
            width="100%"
            height="100%"
            style="border:0;"
            allowfullscreen=""
            loading="lazy"
            referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[24rem,minmax(24rem,1fr)]">
        <FAQCard question="Eligibility" cardId={"eligibility"}>
          Anyone 13–18 is welcome! If you're in middle school or a gap year student, check
          in with us at <a
            class="underline"
            href="mailto:apocalypse@hackclub.com"
            target="_blank">apocalypse@hackclub.com</a
          >. Don't forget to bring an ID that includes a photo! Read our policy <a
            class="underline"
            href="https://apocalypse.hackclub.com/id">here</a
          >.
        </FAQCard>

        <FAQCard question="Travel grants" cardId={"travel-grants"}>
          <p class="font-sans text-sm lg:text-base">
            Apocalypse is for hackers across Canada and the world. If you need help paying
            for travel costs, you've got options!
          </p>
          <p class="font-sans text-sm lg:text-base">
            <span class="font-bold underline">Travelling by car, bus, or train?</span> The
            Hack Club Gas Fund can reimburse your costs. Learn more <a
              href="https://gas.hackclub.com"
              class="underline"
              target="_blank">here</a
            >.
            <p class="font-sans text-sm lg:text-base">
              <span class="font-bold underline">Flying in?</span> We have a limited amount
              of grants available. Please indicate your interest on the registration form.
              Looking for the travel grant application? It's <a
                href="https://join.apocalypse.hackclub.com/grants"
                class="underline"
                target="_blank">over here</a
              >!
            </p>
          </p>
        </FAQCard>

        <FAQCard question="Is this free?" cardId={1}>
          Yep. Attending costs a grand total of $0. Zilch. Nada. Nothing. From meals to
          mini-events, Apocalypse is universally accessible.
        </FAQCard>

        <FAQCard question="I’m new to coding, can I join?" cardId={3}>
          Apocalypse is for hackers of all skill levels. We’ll learn more together at
          workshops! If you want to start learning from home, YouTube and <a
            class="underline"
            href="https://workshops.hackclub.com/"
            target="_blank">these workshops</a
          >
           are awesome. If nothing else, you can learn surprisingly fast at a hackathon :)
        </FAQCard>

        <FAQCard question="Do I need a team?" cardId={4}>
          Not required, but highly encouraged! You can meet teammates at Apocalypse, too
          :) Teams are limited to 4 hackers.
        </FAQCard>

        <FAQCard question="What should I bring?" cardId={5}>
          Please bring an official ID that includes a photo (read <a
            class="underline"
            href="https://apocalypse.hackclub.com/id">the full policy</a
          >), laptop ⚡ <span class="font-bold">with its charger</span> ⚡, sleeping bag,
          toiletries, water bottle, and imagination.
        </FAQCard>

        <FAQCard question="My parents are worried—what should I do?" cardId={6}>
          Apocalypse will have 24/7 supervision by background-checked adults, with venue
          access limited to participants.<br /> Our parent's guide is available <a
            href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1NQDChsJd9dK4r1EWsVglzjHr0EnR3iW0DV3xMHSUAZ0/edit?usp=sharing"
            target="_blank"
            class="underline">here</a
          >. Please reach out to <a
            class="underline"
            href="mailto:apocalypse@hackclub.com"
            target="_blank">apocalypse@hackclub.com</a
          > with any concerns.
        </FAQCard>

        <FAQCard question="Who’s running this?" cardId={7}>
          Apocalypse is organized by an eclectic group of teens who've worked on
          hackathons across the world! We're part of Hack Club, an 8-year old nonprofit
          organization whose mission is to foster a wholesome generation of coders,
          makers, founders and builders. Watch a recap of Outernet, Hack Club's summer
          2023 hackathon, <a
            class="underline"
            href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O1s5HqSqKi0">here</a
          >.
        </FAQCard>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

